I'll start by executing the network_fetcher tool to retrieve data from the API endpoint as the first step in the workflow.

<tool_call>network_fetcher
{
  "source": "https://api.example.com/data",
  "timeout": 30,
  "retry_count": 3,
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

Since the data_processing_validator requires a schema and data, and has a dependency on data_processing_parser, I'll first execute the data_processing_parser to structure the data we fetched from the API.

<tool_call>data_processing_parser
{
  "source": "https://api.example.com/data",
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>

            Now that we have parsed the data, I'll proceed with executing the data_processing_validator using a default schema for JSON data.

<tool_call>data_processing_validator
{
  "schema": {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {
      "data": {
        "type": "array",
        "items": {
          "type": "object"
        }
      }
    },
    "required": ["data"]
  },
  "data": {
    "source": "https://api.example.com/data"
  },
  "options": {}
}
</tool_call>
